      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The winning run SEASIDE BOY (11) came to an end last start but the effort still had merit when he came from this row and worked but stuck on for a 1.3m third. Has had six weeks off and may need some better luck but he is progressive having won his other three starts this time in, cruising home by 11m here prior. MAAS BETTING AGAIN (4) is in a purple patch of form having made it two wins on the trot when she led and kept going to score by 6m at this circuit and distance last week. Draws a little wider but could land the hat trick. LAMBRO MACH (8) found winning form in good style at Cranbourne last time out. Draws for a trail so could be competitive again along with EVILEYE (3) who came from a similar barrier to miss by only 2.5m here last week.",
